    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A radar system that uses the motion of the vehicle (such as a spacecraft) carrying it to simulate a system having a much larger antenna area and that is used to obtain high-resolution images of a surface (as of a planet). It requires that the radar be moving in a straight line, either on an airplane or orbiting in space.</Note_Text>
